{"type":"message","id":"10ffdb08","parentId":"46d3fed7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:45:05.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_spqa814ln9ux_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Holds — Topics to Revisit Later\n\n> Use `/hold1`, `/hold2`, etc. to save topics. `/holds` to see all. `/clearhold1` to clear.\n\n## Active Holds\n\n### /hold1 — Causal-minimal project\nBuild a minimal causal reasoning system:\n- State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n- Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n- Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n- Test: does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n- Location: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n- Status: design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n\n### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Model picked:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active per token, 35B total)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Q4_K_M: 20GB VRAM — fits A5000 30GB with headroom\n  - Base: Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B (multilingual, strong reasoning)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Model picked, awaiting Paperspace notebook setup\n\n---\n\n## Archive (cleared holds)\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774143905592}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3bd1d6f","parentId":"10ffdb08","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:45:11.319Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There it is. Two holds:\n1. /hold1 - Causal-minimal project (build a minimal causal reasoning system)\n2. /hold2 - Build our own gateway (replace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own, running on Paperspace Gradient)\n\nSo Zach wants to work on /hold2 — building our own gateway to replace OpenClaw's agent loop, with the model running on Paperspace Gradient. Let me dig into this and understand what needs to happen. The TOOLS.md already mentions:\n- Remote GPU: A5000 on Paperspace Gradient\n- Model picked: Qwen3.5-35B\n\nLet me look at what the current status is and what needs to be done.","thinkingSignature":"9edd8660bc55d349de75b6ae1f6e09e8372d1150dea20441000b3972fdd96836"},{"type":"text","text":"Found `/hold2` — building our own gateway with the Qwen model on Paperspace Gradient. This is the one where we replace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer running on the A5000.\n\nWhat's the first step — spinning up the Paperspace notebook with vLLM, or something else?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5068,"output":217,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17693,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774143905594}}
