{"type":"message","id":"2fb97ae5","parentId":"3ea1e32c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T02:10:18.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is clarifying that the Paperspace machine isn't an A5000 — it's either a P5000 or RTX5000, both with 8 CPU cores and 30GB VRAM. I need to think about which one I'd prefer for running the Qwen3.5-35B model.\n\nThe key specs that matter:\n- Both have 30GB VRAM (same as I thought for A5000)\n- Both have 8 CPU cores\n\nFor running Qwen3.5-35B with Q4_K_M quantization (~20GB VRAM), both would work fine in terms of VRAM. The difference would be in GPU compute power, memory bandwidth, etc.\n\n\nThe P5000 uses Pascal architecture while the RTX 5000 is based on Turing — the RTX 5000 is newer with better compute and memory bandwidth, making it the stronger choice for inference workloads like this one.","thinkingSignature":"4b334d298dd19616883a917a3f4f9d327c5ddda76792e688ca1b6caa4ef350c0"},{"type":"text","text":"RTX 5000 — newer architecture (Turing vs Pascal), better memory bandwidth and compute. It'll run the Qwen model faster and handle the vLLM inference loop more efficiently. P5000 is no slouch but RTX 5000 is the clear winner here."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":243,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17577,"totalTokens":17863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774145409215}}
