{"type":"message","id":"a2aadc28","parentId":"31626130","timestamp":"2026-03-22T02:46:13.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a typo — `--device cuda` isn't a valid flag. The correct flag for vLLM is `--device cuda` but looking at the usage output, I don't see a `--device` flag at all. For vLLM the GPU is auto-detected. Also `--dtype half` should be `--dtype float16` or just remove it. Let me check the correct flags.\n\nLooking at the error: `unrecognized arguments: --devicer` - it seems `--device` was parsed as `--devicer` which means it doesn't recognize it.\n\nThe correct vLLM command is simpler. Let me give the right one:\n```\npython -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive --dtype half --port 8000\n\n\n```\n\nThe `--device cuda` flag isn't actually supported by vLLM — it just needs CUDA available, which we already have. I should also consider adding `--gpu-memory-utilization 0.9` to allocate most of the available VRAM, or let vLLM detect it automatically.","thinkingSignature":"52e4c3516bea262beb9c82f5d488bb30107e9f16154fe402c687f8285fac7ce6"},{"type":"text","text":"Typo — `--device` isn't a vLLM flag. Run this instead:\n\n```\npython -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive --dtype half --port 8000\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":305,"cacheRead":28571,"cacheWrite":4900,"totalTokens":33819,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774147562757}}
