{"type":"message","id":"24eb0546","parentId":"507179ff","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:10:02.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that vLLM expects a config.json in the model directory, but this is a GGUF file which is a raw quantized file without the usual HuggingFace model structure. vLLM 0.18.0 supports GGUF models through the `gguf` loader, but the path handling is different.\n\nLet me check what files are actually in the model directory - it only downloaded the `.gguf` file, not the full model structure. vLLM needs the actual model files or a proper HuggingFace format.\n\nThe Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive model on HuggingFace is a GGUF quantized model. \n\nFor vLLM to work with GGUF files, I need to point it directly to the `.gguf` file itself rather than the directory. I should try specifying the exact file path with `--tensor-parallel-size 1` since this is a single GPU setup, or check if there's a `Qwen3.5-35B-A3B` base model that could work instead.","thinkingSignature":"5148bd2870debf23f3673bb6505cd5b8df757683642b9a63edd5e954dd1df65d"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue is vLLM needs the actual model files, not just the GGUF — and we only grabbed the quant. Let's get the full model instead:\n\n```\nrm -rf /notebooks/model\nhuggingface-cli download HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive --local-dir /notebooks/model --include \"config.json\" \"model.safetensors\" \"tokenizer*\"\n```\n\nThat'll pull the actual model files + tokenizer. This repo is probably structured as a GGUF model with separate files — check what's actually there first:\n\n```\nls -la /notebooks/model/\n```\n\nRun that and we'll see what we're working with."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":374,"cacheRead":38735,"cacheWrite":2502,"totalTokens":41654,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774148986295}}
