{"type":"message","id":"f09db6b3","parentId":"4d4efa83","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:15:35.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, 428TB total and 185TB available?! That's a network filesystem (the addresses look like Paperspace's distributed storage). But \"10.0.3.160:6789\" looks like GlusterFS or something similar. The `/notebooks` directory is mounted network storage.\n\nBut earlier they said \"150GB or drive\" — that might have been a mistake or that was the root filesystem size estimate. With 185TB available, space isn't the issue.\n\nBut they said downloading the full model failed with \"too big to download that one\". Maybe the 428TB is a network mount and there's a quota at the `/notebooks` level specifically? Or maybe they hit a file size limit on the Paperspace side?\n \nActually, those addresses in the mount point are Paperspace's network blockstore — 185TB of actual available space is substantial, so the issue is likely something else. When they tried downloading the full model without filters, it failed with \"too big to download that one\", but the 21.2GB Q4_K_M variant worked fine. This suggests either a file size limit on Paperspace's end or something else is constraining the download.\n\nWait, looking back at the first download attempt — it actually completed the Q4_K_M download successfully. The error about \"Disk quota exceeded\" happened during the partial download of a different variant. So space wasn't the bottleneck; something else went wrong with that initial download attempt.\n\nLet me trace through what actually happened: the full repo pull would have been around 69GB total (multiple quant variants plus model files), but they only had 150GB of local disk. Paperspace must be using a different storage backend — the 185TB available is network storage, but `/notebooks` itself has its own 150GB quota that they mentioned earlier.\n\nThe Q4_K_M variant worked fine at 21.2GB, but the full model is too large to download. So I need to figure out what files are actually required to run the model and whether vLLM can work with the GGUF format directly, or if we need to download just the specific files it needs.","thinkingSignature":"3ffe29dbd417710b633ef529bda054d1331bb7604bf22c65b1271af0613ec9ca"},{"type":"text","text":"185TB available — that mount has plenty of space. The issue must be a per-file or per-session quota on Paperspace's network mount. \n\nWe need to find out what vLLM actually needs from this repo. Check what files the Q4_K_M GGUF needs:\n\n```\nls -la /notebooks/model/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"empty\"\nfind /notebooks/.cache -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"*.txt\" 2>/dev/null | head -20\n```\n\nAnd separately — can you check the HuggingFace repo page directly? The URL would be:\n`https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n\nIf you can share what's on that page (files listed, sizes), we can download just what vLLM needs."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":626,"cacheRead":44246,"cacheWrite":169,"totalTokens":45084,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774149314079}}
