{"type":"message","id":"883502aa","parentId":"9e0d15a6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:17:03.910Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web fetch isn't returning useful content. Let me try to use the HF API directly. Actually, maybe I should check the files another way.\n\nActually, the important thing I noticed from the ls output is that the repo contains:\n- Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q8_0.gguf (36.9GB)\n- mmproj-Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-f16.gguf (899MB)\n- README.md\n- .gitattributes\n\nThe Q4_K_M was 21.2GB. \n\nThe Q8_0 is 37GB. So the disk has 50GB free. The Q4_K_M is 21GB. So why did the previous download with Q4_K_M succeed (21GB) but the one with Q8_0 fail? Unless the Q8_0 file is what's currently there and the disk filled up. I think the download partially completed and then the disk filled up before the move could finish. Let me check what's actually in the model directory right now and verify the free space again. Also, vLLM 0.18 should be able to handle GGUF files directly—I might just need to point it at the Q4_K_M file specifically. The Q8_0 is 37GB, Q4_K_M is 21GB. 50GB free. Q4_K_M should fit easily. So the problem was the previous downloads of Q5_K_M and other files which bloated the cache. When we cleaned up and did the Q4_K_M only, it worked. But then we deleted the model directory with Q4_K_M in it, so we lost the downloaded file. The Q8_0 might be a partial download from before or something else. I think the best path forward is to have Zach re-download Q4_K_M with a clear mind, check the disk space to confirm we have enough room, and then proceed with running the vLLM server.\n\nNow I'm realizing the real bottleneck: Paperspace's network mount has a 150GB quota, not a disk space problem. The cache was being stored on that same mount, which is why we hit the limit. The Q4_K_M file alone is 21.2GB, so it should fit within the 50GB free space we have available. If we download to /tmp instead of the mount, we can work around this constraint and then run vLLM from the downloaded location.\n\nLet me have Zach download the Q4_K_M file to /tmp and check what's currently in the model directory.","thinkingSignature":"c9799d39c908a582e0307f32468ae89080e8f89dded6713bb2df6870dd6898a1"},{"type":"text","text":"The Paperspace network mount has a 150GB quota — that's why it failed. 150GB total, not 150GB free. The Q8_0 (37GB) already ate into that.\n\nCheck the current state:\n```\nls -la /notebooks/model/\ndf -h /notebooks\n```\n\nIf we still have room for Q4_K_M (21GB), download it to `/tmp` instead to avoid the mount quota:\n\n```\nhuggingface-cli download HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive --local-dir /tmp/model --include \"*Q4_K_M*\"\n```\n\nThen run vLLM from `/tmp/model`."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35150,"output":697,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48255,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774149406884}}
