{"type":"message","id":"334620e0","parentId":"b7adcbe9","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:22:22.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is the same - vLLM doesn't natively support GGUF format. It needs the model in HuggingFace format (safetensors + config.json). GGUF support in vLLM requires either:\n1. Using `llama.cpp` server (`llama-server` from `llama-cpp-python`)\n2. Converting the GGUF to a format vLLM understands\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - vLLM 0.18 DOES support GGUF via `--quantization gptq` or similar? No wait, that's not right either.\n\nThe real issue: this is a GGUF-only model repo. The model is ONLY available as GGUF files, not as regular safetensors. \n\nvLLM can't load GGUF directly, so I need to use `llama.cpp` with their Python bindings instead. The `llama-cpp-python` package provides an OpenAI-compatible server that can handle GGUF files. I should install it and use `llama-server` to serve the model on port 8000.","thinkingSignature":"74d0876dd27fa26615a71aef23fbc0022bfaa86828c07b788661234fa9b36679"},{"type":"text","text":"vLLM doesn't load GGUF directly — this repo is GGUF-only. We need `llama.cpp` server instead:\n\n```\npip install llama-cpp-python[server]\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```\npython -m llama_cpp.server --model /tmp/model/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q4_K_M.gguf --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --n-gpu-layers 99\n```\n\nThis will serve the model with an OpenAI-compatible API that OpenClaw can call."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":342,"cacheRead":48217,"cacheWrite":2702,"totalTokens":51304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774149729868}}
