{"type":"message","id":"d12de103","parentId":"418b5c60","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:26:53.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 doesn't support the Qwen3 MoE architecture (`qwen35moe`). This is a known limitation — llama.cpp added Qwen3 MoE support more recently.\n\nOptions:\n1. Upgrade llama-cpp-python to a newer version that supports Qwen3 MoE\n2. Use a different backend that supports GGUF with Qwen3 MoE\n\nLet me check what version of llama.cpp is bundled with llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 and whether it supports qwen35moe. Actually, let me try a different approach — use the `gguf-py` or try to find a newer build of llama-cpp-python.\n\n\nI should look for a newer release of llama-cpp-python that's compatible with Qwen3 MoE, or potentially use a pre-built binary with CUDA support.","thinkingSignature":"a26cdb35f4394b225848d4841040caf37c5b78c54c5d8949ad25541d66346da8"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe installed llama-cpp-python (0.3.16) doesn't support Qwen3 MoE architecture yet. Need a newer version. Check for CUDA-enabled build:\n\n```\npip install llama-cpp-python[server] --force-reinstall --index-url https://abetlen.github.io/llama-cpp-python/whl/cu121\n```\n\nOr if that fails, try upgrading to latest from source:\n\n```\npip install llama-cpp-python[server] --force-reinstall --no-binary :all:\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":285,"cacheRead":51266,"cacheWrite":3570,"totalTokens":55164,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774149998818}}
