{"type":"message","id":"ba197562","parentId":"a2648ea8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:31:25.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the cu124 index is being used but it's resolving to old versions because of the extra-index-url not being properly configured. Also the typing_extensions conflict - we need typing-extensions>=4.5.0 which should be fine since we have 4.15.0.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The real issue is:\n1. We installed llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 originally from PyPI (no GPU support built-in)\n2. We need a version with CUDA support that supports qwen35moe architecture\n\nThe pre-built CUDA wheels from the extra-index-url are outdated (v0.2.x) and still have the same architecture problem. \n\nBuilding from source might be the way to go, though it could take 30+ minutes. Or I could try specifying an exact version - either grab a recent cu124 wheel like v0.3.16 or v0.3.15 from that index and force-reinstall it, or just build from source. But actually, I'm realizing llama-cpp-python's CUDA support comes from llama.cpp compiled with CUDA, so the real question is whether the version we're trying to install actually supports qwen35moe.\n\nLooking at llama.cpp's model architecture support, qwen35moe landed in llama.cpp around July-August 2025, which means any reasonably recent version should have it. The real issue might be that the pip-installed version wasn't compiled with CUDA in the first place. Let me try targeting a specific recent version with proper CUDA support - either 0.3.15 or 0.3.16 for cu124 - by forcing that exact version and installing fresh.","thinkingSignature":"2214fa3bf95bb7240dd93cbbe37af7665fb86458979c67e4da326714b5221f15"},{"type":"text","text":"Those are all cu121 versions, not cu124. We need cu124 for CUDA 12.4. Try specifying the version directly:\n\n```\npip install llama-cpp-python==0.3.16 --force-reinstall --extra-index-url https://abetlen.github.io/llama-cpp-python/whl/cu124\n```\n\nIf that fails, let's check what's actually available for cu124:\n```\npip index versions llama-cpp-python --extra-index-url https://abetlen.github.io/llama-cpp-python/whl/cu124 2>&1 | head -30\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":464,"cacheRead":56638,"cacheWrite":2219,"totalTokens":59364,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774150269589}}
