{"type":"message","id":"03ea548a","parentId":"6cdf3ac6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:32:40.062Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 IS installed with CUDA support (the cu124 version). The issue was that when we tried `--extra-index-url https://abetlen.github.io/llama-cpp-python/whl/cu124`, it installed from cu124. \n\nBut the problem is that llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 still doesn't support `qwen35moe` architecture. The error was \"unknown model architecture: 'qwen35moe'\".\n\nThe Qwen3.5 MoE architecture (`qwen35moe`) was only added to llama.cpp recently. We need a version of llama-cpp-python that has the GGUF k-quants support for Qwen3 MoE. \n\nQwen3 was released in March 2025, so I need to verify whether the current llama-cpp-python version actually supports it or if we need to build from source with a newer commit that adds Qwen3 MoE architecture support. icroarchitectures.\n\nLet me think... Qwen3 was released by Alibaba in March 2025. The llama.cpp project added Qwen3 support around that time. The version 0.3.16 might not have Qwen3 MoE support yet.\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully:\n```\nllama_model_load: error loading model: error loading model architecture: unknown model architecture: 'qwen35moe'\n```\n\nThis means llama.cpp's model loading code doesn't recognize `qwen35moe`. The GGUF file has `general.architecture = qwen35moe` in its metadata, which is the architecture identifier used by the tokenizer config in the GGUF file.\n\nThe issue is that llama.cpp needs to recognize this architecture. If the installed llama-cpp-python 0.3.16 was built against a llama.cpp version that doesn't know about `qwen35moe`, it won't work.\n\nThe solution would be to build from source with a recent llama.cpp that supports Qwen3 MoE, or find a pre-built wheel with this support. The HauhauCS model quantizer might have added special handling, so I should try the regular Qwen3.5-35B model from HuggingFace instead of this custom quantized version, or check if there's a specific build of llama-cpp-python that supports this architecture.","thinkingSignature":"69d37c3251dde47ce2fc22527db6acd86a3d0a825066ac8d24f90cf6a9381d00"},{"type":"text","text":"The 0.3.16 cu124 is installed — but it still failed because `qwen35moe` architecture isn't supported in this build. This model is a custom GGUF quant that may need a bleeding-edge llama.cpp build.\n\nTwo options:\n\n**Option 1 — Build from source (takes ~10 min):**\n```\npip uninstall llama-cpp-python -y\nCMAKE_ARGS=\"-DLLAMA_CUBLAS=ON\" pip install llama-cpp-python[server] --no-binary :all:\n```\n\n**Option 2 — Try a different model instead:**\nUse the base `Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B` from HuggingFace directly with vLLM (not GGUF). We'd download the safetensors version which vLLM handles natively.\n\nWhich do you want to try? Option 1 is more correct but takes time. Option 2 might be faster if the disk space works out."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":673,"cacheRead":56842,"cacheWrite":5837,"totalTokens":63395,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774150334951}}
