{"type":"compaction","id":"01c1703b","parentId":"bd665ac2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:39:30.227Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **GPU**: RTX 5000 (16GB VRAM, 30GB RAM, 150GB disk) — Turing architecture, superior to P5000 Pascal\n- **Model**: HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive with Q4_K_M quant (~21.2GB)\n- **Paperspace template**: PyTorch base, install vLLM on top\n- **Container**: vllm/vllm-openai:latest via custom container (deferred, used pip install instead)\n- **vLLM command**: `python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model /notebooks/model --dtype half --port 8000 --trust-remote-code`\n- **Continuity requirement**: Zach insisted Nova act as ONE persistent entity across /new sessions, not re-introduce on reconnect\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Get vLLM to load the Qwen model successfully — currently blocked because downloaded GGUF file lacks required HuggingFace model structure (config.json, tokenizer files)\n- Explore whether vLLM 0.18.0 supports GGUF direct loading or if we need to re-download the full model with proper structure\n- Address remaining pip dependency conflicts (tensorflow, spacy, deepspeed, etc.)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- 150GB disk limit on Paperspace — full model download exhausted quota; must use targeted downloads\n- NumPy must stay <2 due to TensorFlow 2.15.0 incompatibility with numpy 2.x\n- RTX 5000 only has 16GB VRAM — Q4_K_M (~21GB) requires memory-mapping some weights to RAM\n\n## Pending user asks\n- (none — conversation is active, user is cooperating)\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Model repo: `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n- GGUF file: `Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q4_K_M.gguf` (21.2GB)\n- Paperspace notebook hostname: `nc8m0mv0sr`\n- Paperspace URL: `https://nc8m0mv0sr.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com`\n- Jupyter token: `3aee14b919811ff001979300f361690a`\n- Jupyter running on ports 8888/8889\n- vLLM version: 0.18.0\n- PyTorch version: 2.10.0 (upgraded from 2.1.1+cu121)\n- NumPy version: 1.26.4 (downgraded from 2.2.6)\n- GPU: Quadro RTX 5000, 16384MiB VRAM, CUDA 12.4, Driver 550.144.03\n- vLLM server command attempted: `python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model /notebooks/model --dtype half --port 8000 --trust-remote-code`\n- Error received: `Value error, Invalid repository ID or local directory specified: '/notebooks/model'` — missing config.json/model structure\n- Holds file: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\holds.md`\n- Memory file: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY.md`\n- Date/time: Saturday March 21, 2026, 9:39 PM EDT through 11:11 PM EDT\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- This is a GGUF-only repo without standard HuggingFace model files (no config.json, model.safetensors, etc.)\n- The Q8_0 quant (37GB) won't fit in available 50GB storage\n- Need to download Q4_K_M specifically, but `--include` filters are not matching any files\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Download the Q4_K_M GGUF quantization file\n- Figure out how to load GGUF directly with vLLM 0.18 (may need `--quantization ggml` flag or llama.cpp server)\n- Verify if base model files exist elsewhere or if GGUF-only loading is required\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Storage limited to ~50GB free space\n- Need to fit model in available space\n- vLLM 0.18 available for serving\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Download and run the Q4_K_M quantized version of HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive model\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **User**: Ton0Fun (ID: 8371302588)\n- **Message ID**: 4244\n- **Timestamp**: Sat 2026-03-21 23:16 EDT (Sat Mar 22 03:16 UTC)\n- **HuggingFace Repo**: HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive\n- **Model file (Q8_0)**: Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q8_0.gguf (36.9GB / 36903139392 bytes)\n- **Multimodal projector**: mmproj-Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-f16.gguf (899MB / 899283040 bytes)\n- **Cache path**: /notebooks/.cache\n- **Model path**: /notebooks/model\n- **API endpoint**: https://huggingface.co/api/models/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive?blobs=true\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4235\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:13 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nits too big to download that one]\n- Assistant: How much free space is left on the machine?\n\n```\ndf -h /notebooks\n```\n\nAnd while that's running — vLLM 0.18 might support GGUF directly with the right loader. We might need `llama.cpp` server instead if vLLM can't load it. Let's see what space we have first.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4238\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:15 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nroot@nc8m0mv0sr:/notebooks# df -h /notebooks\nFilesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on\n10.0.3.160:6789,10.0.3.161:6789,10.0.3.158:6789:/ 428T 244T 185T 57% /notebooks\nroot@nc8m0mv0sr:/notebooks#\n- Assistant: 185TB available — that mount has plenty of space. The issue must be a per-file or per-session quota on Paperspace's network mount. \n\nWe need to find out what vLLM actually needs from this repo. Check what files the Q4_K_M GGUF needs:\n\n```\nls -la /notebooks/model/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"empty\"\nfind /notebooks/.cache -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"*.txt\" 2>/dev/null | head -20\n```\n\nAnd separately — can you check the HuggingFace repo page directly? The URL would be:\n`https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n\nIf you can share what's on that page (files listed, sizes)...\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4241\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:15 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\n50.7 GiB | 150 GiB\n- Assistant: 50GB free — the full model is ~50GB so we're tight but possible. The Q4_K_M we have is 21GB. Let's see what vLLM actually needs to load GGUF.\n\nCheck if there's a `config.json` cached anywhere from the first partial download, and also what the HuggingFace page shows:\n\n```\nfind /root/.cache/huggingface -name \"config.json\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\n```\n\nAnd open this on your browser and tell me what files are listed:\n`https://huggingface.co/HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive/tree/main`\n\nThe GGUF files should be there alongside the config and tokenizer files. We just need to downl...\n\n<read-files>\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\holds.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\MEMORY.md\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY.md\n</modified-files>\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n5. Read `CONTEXT.md` — understand the context management system\n6. Read `memory/active-projects.md` — know what's hot right now\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (