{"type":"message","id":"bc496204","parentId":"1fee68cb","timestamp":"2026-03-22T03:45:42.478Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach has two questions:\n1. How to set up shell/CLI access - this seems to be about accessing OpenClaw from CLI\n2. How to let me control VS Code or an IDE\n\nFor question 1, OpenClaw has a gateway that can be controlled via CLI. Looking at the help output, there are commands like `openclaw agent --to ...` which suggests there's a way to send messages via CLI.\n\nFor question 2, letting me control VS Code - this could mean:\n- VS Code has a CLI interface (`code --remote`)\n- There's a VS Code extension for OpenClaw\n- Or using the VS Code server mode\n\nLet me think about what's actually available. OpenClaw docs are at C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs. Let me check what CLI docs exist.\n\n\nLooking at the available files, I should check the CLI documentation to understand what commands are actually supported.","thinkingSignature":"aeafdb669af5d95fbc1c95dddf739dfc2a6fe121d908855afd37582d9dbb6812"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4dvzrf2ttaji_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":256,"cacheRead":37066,"cacheWrite":3016,"totalTokens":40381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774151133139}}
