ds:\n- ✅ Paperspace Gradient notebook (the Linux server we've been using)\n- ❌ Your local Windows machine (no access path)\n\nFor Chrome debugging to work, Chrome would need to be running on a machine I *can* reach — either the Paperspace machine (but there's no browser there, just a terminal) or your local PC (which I can't access directly).\n\nThe options are:\n1. **SSH tunnel** — you tunnel your local Chrome's debug port to Paperspace so I can reach it: `ssh -L 9222:localhost:9222 paperspace`\n2. **Remote.it / ngrok** — expose your local Chrome to the internet\n3. **Let me fix the llama.cpp build on Paperspace** instead — then we don't need Chrome at all\n\nWhich route interests you?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":537,"cacheRead":47766,"cacheWrite":32,"totalTokens":48378,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774151300554}}
