{"type":"message","id":"260390f8","parentId":"f4b1f208","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:09:58.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me get the languages breakdown and the README content.","thinkingSignature":"2928c9d21aa01ff84cf02db620868ca070f9af3a6ba58c943ea75f9c23941964"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qb9a2h3pd9i9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/toxzak-svg/particleblood-rust-gpu/languages\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56930,"output":77,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69415,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774152588910}}
{"type":"message","id":"24c59fc7","parentId":"260390f8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:10:00.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qb9a2h3pd9i9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"Rust\": 122886,\n  \"JavaScript\": 60843,\n  \"CSS\": 10292,\n  \"HTML\": 7687\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1390,"aggregated":"{\n  \"Rust\": 122886,\n  \"JavaScript\": 60843,\n  \"CSS\": 10292,\n  \"HTML\": 7687\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774152600052}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5a58f28","parentId":"24c59fc7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:10:05.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me get the README content.","thinkingSignature":"962d5f9f8624d4114151b7fcfb7df9fd26aec29a0064d8aebbab0f70265e4971"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n0p95owsxy5g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/toxzak-svg/particleblood-rust-gpu/readme\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; import base64; data=json.load(sys.stdin); print(base64.b64decode(data['content']).decode('utf-8'))\" 2>&1 | head -100","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57056,"output":121,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774152600057}}
{"type":"message","id":"fab59876","parentId":"d5a58f28","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:10:06.220Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n0p95owsxy5g_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# RustyParts\r\n\r\nInteractive particle-field app built with Rust + WebAssembly and rendered with WebGL2.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- High-density particle simulation on GPU\r\n- Shape form/melt interaction\r\n- Brush modes: push, pull, vortex\r\n- FX presets and color controls\r\n- Attractor controls and live particle count display\r\n- **Shareable moment**: one-shot link that plays once and melts away (see below)\r\n\r\n## Run (Web)\r\n\r\nFrom workspace root:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncd rustyparts\r\ntrunk serve\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen open the local URL shown by Trunk.\r\n\r\n## Build Check\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncargo check\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Controls\r\n\r\n- Pointer move: apply brush force\r\n- Hold click/touch: enable attractor at pointer\r\n- Tap/click: toggle shape visibility\r\n- Wheel: adjust attractor mass\r\n- Q/W/E: brush mode\r\n- Z/X/C: quality preset\r\n- 1/2/3: FX preset\r\n- Enter: form shape text\r\n- M: melt shape\r\n- T: switch shape layout\r\n\r\n## Shareable moment (story mode)\r\n\r\nShare a link that plays **once** and then shows ôThis moment is gone.ö\r\n\r\n- **URL**: `?m=1` for story mode; optional `&t=Your+Message` (up to 18 chars, forms then melts).\r\n- **Example**: `https://yoursite.com/?m=1&t=Hello` ù opens to your message forming, holding, then melting; after that, reopening the same link in that browser shows only ôThis moment is gone.ö\r\n- **OG/Twitter**: Basic meta tags are set for social previews.\r\n\r\n## Mobile\r\n\r\n- **Haptics**: Touch interactions trigger short vibration (light on touch, pattern on release burst). Form/Melt buttons trigger medium haptics. Requires a device and browser that support the Vibration API (e.g. Android Chrome; not supported in Safari).\r\n- **Share**: Use the Share button to share the link (Web Share API when available, otherwise copy link). No permissions required.\r\n\r\n## Project Files\r\n\r\n- src/lib.rs: Rust app logic + shader sources\r\n- styles.css: UI styling\r\n- index.html: Trunk entry page and controls"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1173,"aggregated":"# RustyParts\r\n\r\nInteractive particle-field app built with Rust + WebAssembly and rendered with WebGL2.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- High-density particle simulation on GPU\r\n- Shape form/melt interaction\r\n- Brush modes: push, pull, vortex\r\n- FX presets and color controls\r\n- Attractor controls and live particle count display\r\n- **Shareable moment**: one-shot link that plays once and melts away (see below)\r\n\r\n## Run (Web)\r\n\r\nFrom workspace root:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncd rustyparts\r\ntrunk serve\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen open the local URL shown by Trunk.\r\n\r\n## Build Check\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncargo check\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Controls\r\n\r\n- Pointer move: apply brush force\r\n- Hold click/touch: enable attractor at pointer\r\n- Tap/click: toggle shape visibility\r\n- Wheel: adjust attractor mass\r\n- Q/W/E: brush mode\r\n- Z/X/C: quality preset\r\n- 1/2/3: FX preset\r\n- Enter: form shape text\r\n- M: melt shape\r\n- T: switch shape layout\r\n\r\n## Shareable moment (story mode)\r\n\r\nShare a link that plays **once** and then shows ôThis moment is gone.ö\r\n\r\n- **URL**: `?m=1` for story mode; optional `&t=Your+Message` (up to 18 chars, forms then melts).\r\n- **Example**: `https://yoursite.com/?m=1&t=Hello` ù opens to your message forming, holding, then melting; after that, reopening the same link in that browser shows only ôThis moment is gone.ö\r\n- **OG/Twitter**: Basic meta tags are set for social previews.\r\n\r\n## Mobile\r\n\r\n- **Haptics**: Touch interactions trigger short vibration (light on touch, pattern on release burst). Form/Melt buttons trigger medium haptics. Requires a device and browser that support the Vibration API (e.g. Android Chrome; not supported in Safari).\r\n- **Share**: Use the Share button to share the link (Web Share API when available, otherwise copy link). No permissions required.\r\n\r\n## Project Files\r\n\r\n- src/lib.rs: Rust app logic + shader sources\r\n- styles.css: UI styling\r\n- index.html: Trunk entry page and controls","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774152606217}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a46dd5a","parentId":"fab59876","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:10:25.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I have a good picture of RustyParts. It's a Rust + WebAssembly + WebGL2 GPU particle simulation with:\n- Shape form/melt interaction\n- Brush modes: push, pull, vortex\n- FX presets and color controls\n- Attractor controls\n- Shareable moment (story mode) with one-shot links\n- Mobile haptics\n- Web Share API\n\nZach wants ideas for what to do that's similar but \"super high value.\" Let me think about what would be high-value variations:\n\n1. **AI-powered particle interactions** — particles that respond to AI-generated forces (e.g., flocking toward what an LLM describes as \"chaotic\")","thinkingSignature":"3640c8baf6430d1c0bce6c8e2555e3dafa0e9d37839a9867181cb4a9db364ea9"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — RustyParts is a Rust/WebAssembly/WebGL2 GPU particle sim with:\n- Shape form/melt, brush modes (push/pull/vortex)\n- Attractors, FX presets, color controls\n- \"Shareable moment\" — one-shot links that play once then melt\n- Mobile haptics + Web Share API\n\n---\n\n**High-value spinoffs:**\n\n**1. RustyFlow** — AI-generated vector field visualizations. Connect to an LLM that outputs field parameters based on text prompts (\"swirling grief,\" \"jagged anxiety\"). Particles follow the generated flow fields. Sell as a tool for artists/therapists/content creators. Differentiation: actual AI-generated visuals, not just preset FX.\n\n**2. RustyChat** — Interactive message visualization. Messages you send become particle shapes that morph and dissolve. Each contact gets a unique color palette and particle behavior (aggressive vs calm vs chaotic). Embeds in messaging apps. Could be a Matrix/Riot plugin or a standalone web widget.\n\n**3. RustyPresence** — Live status indicator. Your Slack/Discord/Holochat status is visualized as a live particle field others can see in real-time. \"DND\" = particles contract into dense mass. \"Away\" = slow drift. \"Active\" = explosive expansion. People pay for premium palettes and behaviors.\n\n**4. RustyForge** — Generative art engine for creators. They describe a scene in text, the GPU renders a particle version. Output as animated wallpaper, profile pic, poster. Built-in marketplace for people to sell/buy prompt presets. Each image is unique (seed-based).\n\n**5. RustyTrace** — Mouse/keyboard tracking as art. Your keystrokes and mouse movements leave particle trails that form persistent, evolving patterns. Becomes a visual fingerprint of your workflow. Could detect anomalies (someone else using your machine).\n\n**Which resonates? I can scope any of these out fully.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57657,"output":543,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70608,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774152606222}}
