{"type":"message","id":"ff658e22","parentId":"2b0363ed","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:19:18.312Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to:\n1. Fix the haptics in RustyParts\n2. Plan and scaffold RustyTrace (and RustyForge to some degree)\n\nLet me start with the haptics fix since it's in the existing codebase. Then scaffold RustyTrace.\n\nFor the haptics fix:\n1. Add \"Vibrate\" to web-sys Cargo.toml features\n2. Add feature detection (check if `navigator.vibrate` exists)\n3. Increase timings\n4. Add visual indicator\n5. Add haptics toggle\n\nFor RustyTrace scaffold, I'll create a new Rust project (or maybe just a subfolder since it's Rust+wasm based on the same engine).\n\n\nI'll start by updating the Cargo.toml for web-sys with the Vibration feature, then add a feature check in the haptic functions, increase the vibration timings, and create a visual indicator for haptic feedback. After that, I'll set up the RustyTrace scaffold as a new Rust project.","thinkingSignature":"5e892f4fd33d3757f00401fae2257cf79ac3f97916634fdf30b78c2c6657aaf8"},{"type":"text","text":"Starting with haptics fix, then scaffolding RustyTrace right after.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2g8zh9bprb8w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\Cargo.toml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":259,"cacheRead":80727,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80986,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774153149427}}
