{"type":"message","id":"b209548e","parentId":"0e435b8f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:19:31.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add \"Vibrate\" to the web-sys features. But I also need to check if `Vibrate` is a feature in web-sys. Let me check the web-sys crate to see what Vibration features are available.\n\nActually, in web-sys 0.3.77, the Vibration API might not be fully supported. Let me just add \"Navigator\" which has the vibrate method. Actually, looking at the code, it uses `self.window.navigator().vibrate_with_duration()` and `vibrate_with_pattern()`. These methods exist on the `Navigator` type in web-sys. Let me check if there's a `Vibrate` feature.\n\n\nLooking at the available features in web-sys, the Vibration API might not be included by default. Rather than getting stuck on this, I'll implement the haptic functions with graceful fallbacks—wrapping the calls in option checks so the app continues working even if vibration isn't available, then I can investigate the web-sys feature support separately.","thinkingSignature":"4d84fcb178eadb3c1a88e6fdc0be12910036a5ee02045fb1034c9b5b84355d69"},{"type":"text","text":"**Step 1 — Fix haptics:**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5429v29iwl1i_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\src\\lib.rs","oldText":"    fn haptic_light(&self) {\n        let _ = self.window.navigator().vibrate_with_duration(8);\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_medium(&self) {\n        let _ = self.window.navigator().vibrate_with_duration(20);\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_burst(&self) {\n        let pattern = js_sys::Array::of3(&8.into(), &35.into(), &12.into());\n        let _ = self.window.navigator().vibrate_with_pattern(pattern.as_ref());\n    }","newText":"    fn haptic_light(&self) {\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            let _ = nav.with_duration(15);\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_medium(&self) {\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            let _ = nav.with_duration(35);\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_burst(&self) {\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            // Charge-dependent burst: short holds = weak buzz, long holds = strong burst\n            let strength = self.state.touch_burst.strength.max(1.0);\n            let pattern = js_sys::Array::of2(\n                &(12.0 * strength).round().max(8.0) as u32,\n                &(30.0 * strength).round().max(15.0) as u32,\n            );\n            let _ = nav.with_pattern(pattern.as_ref());\n        }\n    }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68862,"output":592,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81862,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774153158321}}
