{"type":"message","id":"e867efed","parentId":"5ed185ae","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:20:01.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `touch_burst` is already a state that drives a visual effect. The `trigger_touch_release_burst` function already activates the burst visually — I don't need to add a separate flash. The burst IS the visual indicator.\n\nBut for form/melt haptics, there's no visual feedback currently. Let me add a `haptic_flash` field to AppState that briefly tints the canvas when a haptic fires. Actually, the simplest approach that doesn't require shader changes: I can make the background shader react briefly when `haptic_light` or `haptic_medium` fire by setting a flash timer.\n\nActually, let me look at the existing `uFx` uniform which controls background effects including a pulse. \n\nI can hook into that pulse mechanism to trigger a flash whenever haptics fire — the background shader already has a pulse effect built in that I can leverage for this.","thinkingSignature":"7608da05c472cd21e50d8153c136ca8427b944e195aa5425169104b51ceb574b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rlyg0u0lkltz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\src\\lib.rs","offset":660,"limit":25}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70919,"output":246,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83573,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774153193912}}
