{"type":"message","id":"616861b9","parentId":"8fc7335d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:23:27.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The `Vibrate` feature doesn't exist in web-sys. The Vibration API is actually accessed through `Navigator.vibrate()` method, not as a separate feature. Let me check the actual web-sys API for the Navigator to see if `vibrate()` method exists.Looking at the Navigator feature, I don't see `Vibrate` listed. This means the Vibration API isn't exposed through web-sys directly.\n\nThe original code was using:\n```rust\nself.window.navigator().vibrate_with_duration(8);\nself.window.navigator().vibrate_with_pattern(pattern.as_ref());\n```\n\nThese methods must come from somewhere. Let me check if they're available through `Navigator` in web-sys. The Navigator type in web-sys should have a `vibrate()` method that returns an `Option<Vibration>` or similar.\n\n\nActually, I think I need to use raw JavaScript interop through `wasm_bindgen` to call the navigator.vibrate() method directly, rather than relying on web-sys bindings that don't exist. Let me remove the `Vibrate` feature I added and instead use `web_sys::eval` or a similar mechanism to invoke the JavaScript API directly.","thinkingSignature":"cdc2ec3ec4418c7fa8617263c13d79588befb8f3c56b631bbc262cc060a045fb"},{"type":"text","text":"The `Vibrate` feature doesn't exist in this version of web-sys. The Vibration API isn't exposed through it. The original code used methods that were never actually available.\n\nLet me remove the bad feature and use JavaScript interop instead:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bu6kngqkz1ho_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\Cargo.toml","oldText":"  \"Navigator\",\n  \"Vibrate\",\n  \"Node\",","newText":"  \"Navigator\",\n  \"Node\","}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99981,"output":375,"cacheRead":1240