{"type":"message","id":"854c95eb","parentId":"597d00b1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:23:40.365Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the haptic methods to use JavaScript interop via `wasm_bindgen`. I'll use `web_sys::eval` to call `navigator.vibrate()` directly.\n\nActually, let me check what's available in wasm-bindgen for calling JavaScript. I need to use `wasm_bindgen::JsValue` and `js_sys::eval`.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach would be to use the `js_sys::eval` function to run JavaScript. But a better approach is to use `web_sys::eval` which returns a Promise.\n\nLet me think about the simplest approach. I can use:\n\n\n```rust\nuse wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;\n\n#[wasm_bindgen]\nextern \"C\" {\n    #[wasm_bindgen(js_namespace = navigator)]\n    fn vibrate(pattern: &JsValue) -> bool;\n}\n```\n\nBut `wasm_bindgen` extern blocks need the functions to be defined somewhere. For raw JS interop without imports, I'd need to use `js_sys::eval` and pass the vibrate call as a string, or use `wasm_bindgen_futures::future_to_promise` if I need async handling.\n\nActually, a cleaner approach would be using `web_sys::eval` directly—something like calling ` navigator.vibrate(duration)` through `Function::from_str` and then invoking it with `.call1()`. The haptic methods just need to fire and forget, returning `()` immediately. The real issue is the original methods like `vibrate_with_duration` don't actually exist on the `Navigator` type in wasm-bindgen at all.","thinkingSignature":"6e1baaf8ae5cedc50d2d2f86852e3ce9bc3f73a43f72878fa9007eb44b0be4c4"},{"type":"text","text":"Now rewrite the haptic methods to use raw JavaScript interop:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kwmdoj6cxphb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\src\\lib.rs","offset":1,"limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100394,"output":400,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774153407503}}
