{"type":"message","id":"5bcd064a","parentId":"02718db1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:23:58.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;` is imported. I can use `闭wasm_bindgen::function` to create JavaScript bindings. Let me look for where the `wasm_bindgen` macro might be defining things, or use `js_sys::eval`.\n\nThe simplest approach is to use `js_sys::eval` with a string. For example:\n```rust\njs_sys::eval(&format!(\"navigator.vibrate({})\", 15)).map(|_| ()).ok();\n```\n\nBut `js_sys::eval` returns a `Result<JsValue, JsValue>`. Let me check if `js_sys` is imported (yes it is: `use js_sys::{Float32Array, Math, Reflect};`).","thinkingSignature":"cd57ba1550cacee979709b528916cb5fef2785bc9e597bb80721fd1131c13734"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — `js_sys` is already imported. Now rewrite the haptic methods using `js_sys::eval`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vhbmzzumuydh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\rustyparts\\src\\lib.rs","oldText":"    fn haptic_light(&mut self) {\n        self.state.haptic_flash = 0.4;\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            let _ = nav.with_duration(15);\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_medium(&mut self) {\n        self.state.haptic_flash = 0.7;\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            let _ = nav.with_duration(35);\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn haptic_burst(&mut self) {\n        self.state.haptic_flash = 1.0;\n        if let Some(nav) = self.window.navigator().vibrate() {\n            // Charge-dependent burst: short holds = weak buzz, long holds = strong burst\n            let strength = self.state.touch_burst.strength.max(1.0);\n            let pattern = js_sys::Array::of2(\n                &(12.0 * strength).round().max(8.0) as u32,\n                &(30.0 * strength).round().max(15.0) as u32,\n            );\n            let _ = nav.with_pattern(patte