{"type":"message","id":"7c7164c3","parentId":"077822b8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:45:44.095Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same linker issue. The problem is that `link.exe` from PATH resolves to something unexpected. The error says \"Try 'link --help' for more information\" which is the Git Bash `link` command help. This means `link` from Git Bash is being called instead of the MSVC linker.\n\nThis is a PATH ordering issue. The Rust toolchain uses `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc` which calls `link.exe` from the MSVC toolchain, but something in the PATH is making Git Bash's `link` take precedence.\n\nLet me check what's happening with link.exe:","thinkingSignature":"daec158ea03154fbbf1560d7579be6cdd4511bdfb8889957a3268d80dde08a30"},{"type":"text","text":"Same linker issue — Git Bash `link` is intercepting MSVC's `link.exe`. Let me fix the PATH:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ldh0xk8ycc1g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"where.exe link 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49605,"output":190,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62203,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154732505}}
