{"type":"message","id":"396ed0fe","parentId":"f4245043","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:47:01.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed - Git Bash's `link.exe` is in the PATH before the MSVC linker. I need to either:\n1. Remove Git/bin from PATH temporarily\n2. Use the full path to the MSVC linker\n3. Use `cmd /c` to run cargo with the correct PATH\n\nThe cleanest fix is to run cargo via `cmd /c` with the PATH set correctly, or find the MSVC link.exe and use its full path.\n\nLet me find the MSVC link.exe:","thinkingSignature":"d90ed158bc791248e751d169323280e08d75286adebdd1c25b8aa81e50eaadc2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_27pwuuqf9ivf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"where.exe /r \"C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Visual Studio\" link.exe 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49823,"output":161,"cacheRead":12408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62392,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154815393}}
